TDF Velogames Daily Update

Race Results - Stage 20




Heres the non-spoiler 4min highlight clip on Youtube:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Ze0us3L9co










Polish rider Maciej Bodnar collected the biggest win of his career by winning the Stage 20 Individual Time Trial in Marseille last night. Chris Froome finished strongly only six seconds behind Bodnar to secure his yellow jersey and with it his grip on a fourth Tour De France success. Bardet did not do as well, losing significant time and allowing Uran to jump over him into second. Bardet holds third over Landa by only one second. Michel Kwiatkowski finishied second on the stage, only one second behind fellow Pole Bodnar. Amazing given how much work weve seen Kwiatkowski perform on behalf of his SKY team leader at the front of the peloton over the last three weeks.

The mostly flat 22.5km course was market by a nasty climb with grades of up to 16%. Many of the riders looked pretty awkward climbing this sharp ascent on their TT machines!
